(42, 23, 35, 60, 2, 4, 4, 'chosen of God', 'Chosen of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''chosen of God.'' In Luke, the rulers mock Jesus'' identity as the chosen one, while 1 Peter affirms Jesus as a living stone, also chosen by God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 23, 35, 40, 12, 18, 18, 'the chosen of God', 'Chosen Servant Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''chosen'' in both passages. In Luke, the rulers mock Jesus as ''the chosen of God,'' while in Matthew, God declares His servant as ''my chosen.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 23, 35, 41, 15, 29, 32, 'He saved others; let him save himself', 'Mockery of Jesus on the Cross', 'Both passages emphasize the mockery directed at Jesus during his crucifixion. They highlight the challenge to Jesus to save himself, reflecting the scorn of the rulers and the crowd.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 23, 35, 19, 22, 6, 8, NULL, 'Mockery of the Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the scorn directed at the suffering figure. In Luke, the rulers mock Jesus, paralleling the derision described in Psalms where onlookers ridicule the one who trusts in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 23, 35, 23, 53, 3, 3, NULL, 'Rejection and Despair in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being despised and rejected. In Luke, the rulers mock Jesus, paralleling the description of being ''despised and rejected of men'' in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 23, 36, 19, 69, 21, 21, NULL, 'Mocking and Thirst Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of offering vinegar in response to thirst. This connection highlights the fulfillment of the psalmist''s words in the context of Jesus'' crucifixion.', 'prophecy', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
