(42, 23, 39, 42, 23, 35, 35, 'if thou be Christ, save thyself', 'Mockery of Christ''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the challenge to Jesus'' identity as the Christ. The rulers and the malefactor question his ability to save himself, highlighting their disbelief in his messianic role.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
